
                                            Workers union Numsa says it will be in court to support the Yende family.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The man charged with the murder of Eskom employee Thembisile Yende is expected to appear in the Springs Magistrates Court on Wednesday morning. David Ngwenya is accused of killing Yende in May after he suspected that she was planning to blow the whistle on an alleged copper cable theft syndicate. Workers union Numsa says it will be in court to support the Yende family. Acting spokesperson Phakamile Hlubi says: “She was a Numsa member and we will continue to stand in solidarity with her family.” WATCH: Thembisile Yende remembered  (Edited by Shimoney Regter)